(42, 8, 28, 41, 1, 24, 27, 'What have I to do with thee', 'Recognition of Jesus'' Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus'' identity and authority by unclean spirits. In Luke, the spirit acknowledges Jesus as ''thou Son of God most high,'' while in Mark, the spirit refers to Him as ''the Holy One of God.'' This connection highlights the consistent theme of Jesus'' power over evil.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
